title: [Gyldemar Forest, Plateau]
description: A large depression in the plateau marks what might have once been the foundation of a small building.  A few of the cornerstones remain in place, though each is badly damaged.  No other trace of the building's stones can be seen.

A large depression in the plateau marks what might have once been the foundation of a small building.  A few of the cornerstones remain in place, though the damage to each can be plainly seen even in the night's darkness.  No other trace of the building's stones can be seen.
